e, and everything imports just fine. However, adding maven-resolver 1.4.2 could create conflicts with maven-core 3.1.0, as it's expecting an older version of Aether. The library's POM specifies version 1.4.2, so that’s something to keep in mind. For transforming classes, it might be worth using the stable API. I'm also considering using tools like jdeps or javap to inspect the references within the code.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_68G6fnScSLcwFaXTcszOxxbD|fc_0aad82b47df01032016a3ede74dcc48190ae4e9594ae853128", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmpd=$(mktemp -d); cd $tmpd; curl -sSLO https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/apache/maven/shared/maven-common-artifact-filters/3.1.1/maven-common-artifact-filters-3.1.1.jar; javap -classpath maven-common-artifact-filters-3.1.1.jar -public org.apache.maven.shared.artifact.filter.resolve.transform.SonatypeAetherFilterTransformer org.apache.maven.shared.artifact.filter.resolve.transform.EclipseAetherFilterTransformer org.apache.maven.shared.artifact.filter.collection.ArtifactTransitivityFilter | sed -n '1,220p'; rm -rf $tmpd", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6181, "output": 1272, "cacheRead": 43520, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 50973, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782505059548, "responseId": "resp_0aad82b47df01032016a3ede641cc081908ea5fc6fb232f87d"}}
